result.execSummary:
The defendant Dane M. Burke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:12 PM cases 21CF830, 22CF554 called. Prosecuting attorney Loralee Clark in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Dane M. Burke in court.  Attorney Erika Amundson in court for Dane M. Burke. 
In 22CF554: Defense waives reading of the complaint. Defendant ordered to be fingerprinted. State makes a request for a cash bond citing missed appearances and open files in several counties. Defense responds. 
Court orders a cash bond. Defendant would like to resolve these matters today. 
Off the record to allow time for the defendant to complete paperwork with Attorney Amundson. 
3:34 PM cases re called. Appearances remain the same as previously stated. 
In 22CF554: Defendant waives right to a preliminary hearing and Court accepts waiver. 
In both files: There is an agreement. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
In 21CF830: Defendant pleads No Contest as charged in the Information to Count 2. 
In 22CF554: Defendant pleads Guilty as charged in the Information to Count 1. 
Court accepts pleas, and finds the defendant Guilty. Anything else is dismissed and read in. 
Court withholds sentencing and places defendant on Probation for 18 months with conditions: 
Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
Complete AODA and follow through with recommendations. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
Pay court costs including applicable surcharges. 
In 21CF830 Ct 2 only: 90 days in Jail with Huber or electronic monitoring if the Jail deems it appropriate, all Stayed pending further order of the Court. 
Parties to file a stipulation on jail credit if revoked in 21CF830. No credit in 22CF554. 
All contraband to be destroyed after it is no longer of evidentiary value.
